## UiSystem-A4 i18n Integration Architecture for Remaining Views
**Status:** approved
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** UiSystem-A1

## Overview

Six Vue views still contain hardcoded English strings that bypass the i18n system. This creates a mono-lingual UX and prevents localization. The i18n integration replaces all hardcoded strings with `t()` calls keyed to the existing `vue-i18n` translation system (en.json / zh.json). Additionally, the i18n test file has localStorage mocking issues that prevent reliable test execution.

## Scope

| View | File | Current State | Hardcoded Strings (approx) |
|------|------|---------------|---------------------------|
| ChatsView | `frontend/src/views/ChatsView.vue` | Partially i18n-ized | ~3 strings remaining |
| WikiView | `frontend/src/views/WikiView.vue` | Partially i18n-ized | ~25 strings remaining |
| AgentsConfigView | `frontend/src/views/AgentsConfigView.vue` | Sparse i18n | ~45 strings remaining |
| ProfessionsView | `frontend/src/views/ProfessionsView.vue` | No i18n | ~40 strings remaining |
| SkillsView | `frontend/src/views/SkillsView.vue` | No i18n | ~35 strings remaining |
| ApiSourcesView | `frontend/src/views/ApiSourcesView.vue` | No i18n | ~55 strings remaining |

## Translation Key Namespace Convention

Each view gets a top-level namespace matching its composableView domain:

| Namespace | Keys | Example |
|-----------|------|---------|
| `chat.*` | Chat sidebar, messages, session info | `chat.sessions`, `chat.searchPlaceholder` |
| `wiki.*` | Wiki sidebar, pages, raw files | `wiki.title`, `wiki.newPage`, `wiki.editing` |
| `agents.*` | Agent config cards, edit form | `agents.agentForge`, `agents.createAgent` |
| `professions.*` | Profession cards, edit form | `professions.title`, `professions.addProfession` |
| `skills.*` | Skill cards, edit form | `skills.title`, `skills.addSkill` |
| `apiSources.*` | API source sidebar, detail, scan | `apiSources.title`, `apiSources.testConnection` |
| `common.*` | Shared across views (already exists) | `common.save`, `common.cancel`, `common.delete` |

## Data Flow

```
[User selects locale]
    → vue-i18n switches active locale
    → All t() calls re-evaluate reactively
    → Views render translated strings
    → No page refresh needed
```

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "Translation Files"
        EN[en.json]
        ZH[zh.json]
    end
    subgraph "vue-i18n"
        VI[createI18n]
    end
    subgraph "Views"
        CV[ChatsView]
        WV[WikiView]
        AV[AgentsConfigView]
        PV[ProfessionsView]
        SV[SkillsView]
        ASV[ApiSourcesView]
    end

    EN --> VI
    ZH --> VI
    VI -->|t\(\)| CV
    VI -->|t\(\)| WV
    VI -->|t\(\)| AV
    VI -->|t\(\)| PV
    VI -->|t\(\)| SV
    VI -->|t\(\)| ASV
```

## Trigger Condition

Every view mount and every template re-render triggers `t()` evaluation. The i18n plugin is already installed; this work only adds missing `t()` calls and translation keys.

## Design Highlight

The views that already have partial i18n (ChatsView, WikiView) follow the same pattern — the remaining views simply adopt the established convention. No new infrastructure needed.

### Trade-offs

| Approach | Pros | Cons |
|---|---|---|
| Per-view namespaces (chosen) | Clear ownership, easy to find keys, no collisions | Slightly more keys than flat namespace |
| Flat key namespace | Fewer total keys | Hard to find which view owns a key, collision risk |
| Per-component namespaces | Maximum granularity | Over-engineered for 6 views |

## Test File Fix

The i18n test file has `localStorage` mocking issues under Vitest/jsdom. The fix pattern:

```typescript
// BEFORE (broken): direct localStorage mock conflicts with jsdom
vi.stubGlobal('localStorage', { ... })

// AFTER (working): use vi.spyOn on window.localStorage
const getItemSpy = vi.spyOn(Storage.prototype, 'getItem')
const setItemSpy = vi.spyOn(Storage.prototype, 'setItem')
getItemSpy.mockReturnValue('dark')
```

This avoids replacing the entire Storage object and works correctly with vue-i18n's internal locale persistence.

## UiSystem-A4 i18n View Integration Architecture
**Status:** approved
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** UiSystem-G1

Six Vue views contain hardcoded English strings that prevent localization. ChatsView and WikiView are partially i18n-ized (some `t()` calls exist), while AgentsConfigView, ProfessionsView, SkillsView, and ApiSourcesView are fully hardcoded. The fix is mechanical: replace every hardcoded string with `t('namespace.key')` using the existing vue-i18n setup.

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Translation Layer"
        EN[en.json]
        ZH[zh.json]
        I18N[useI18n composable]
    end

    subgraph "Views — Partially Done"
        CV[ChatsView.vue]
        WV[WikiView.vue]
    end

    subgraph "Views — Fully Hardcoded"
        AC[AgentsConfigView.vue]
        PV[ProfessionsView.vue]
        SV[SkillsView.vue]
        AS[ApiSourcesView.vue]
    end

    EN -->|keys| I18N
    ZH -->|keys| I18N
    I18N -->|t&#40;&#41;| CV
    I18N -->|t&#40;&#41;| WV
    I18N -->|t&#40;&#41;| AC
    I18N -->|t&#40;&#41;| PV
    I18N -->|t&#40;&#41;| SV
    I18N -->|t&#40;&#41;| AS
```

### Key Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| Translation key namespace | Per-view prefix (`agents.`, `professions.`, `skills.`, `apiSources.`, `wiki.`, `chat.`) | Matches existing convention in ChatsView/WikiView |
| Existing `t()` calls | No changes | ChatsView and WikiView already use correct keys; only fill gaps |
| Shared keys | Reuse `common.*` for Edit, Save, Cancel, Delete, Loading, etc. | DRY; these already exist |
| Dynamic strings | Template interpolation `t('key', { count: N })` | vue-i18n built-in; already used for `chat.msgs` |
| Test fix | Correct `localStorage` mock in vi.beforeEach | Standard vitest pattern |

### String Inventory Per View

